  <p>The <i>perlcgi</i> framework can be used to run any CGI script. Like the <xref
        href="1.1index.dita#topic8895/deploying-applications">perl</xref> framework, it provides
      ActivePerl in the default PATH and supports module installation via <xref
        href="1.1index.dita#topic8895/cpan-modules-via-ppm">PPM</xref> and <xref
        href="1.1index.dita#topic8895/cpan-modules-via-cpanm">cpanm</xref>.</p>
  <p>Unlike the perl framework, setting the <i><xref
    href="../../1.1manifestyml.dita#topic20986/start-file">start-file</xref></i> option has
      no effect, as there is no permanently running application. A new instance of a CGI script is
      started for each request.</p>
  <p>Perl scripts deployed with this framework should begin with:</p>
  <codeblock>#!/usr/bin/env perl</codeblock>
